
1. js can be added in three ways 

a. inline : inside html tag 
b. internal : inside html file using script tag
c. external : write on separate file 


2. places where we can inject the file 

1.inside head tag : when we want to execute before the pages loaded  
DisAdvantages : it blocks rendering of page until js not executed 

2.at the end of <body> tag : js executed and loaded after html loaded  : reccomanded 

4. using defer and async 





html vs DOM 

1.html : markup language 
2.DOM : proccessed Elements in document tree in memory ( memory of browser) ;

html is taken in broser and an document tree is generated by the c++ 

